  Nearly 10 years have passed since the day of the tragic loss 
of the Argentine Cruiser General Belgrano that was sunk by the 
British nuclear submarine Conqueror on 2 May 1982. But as 
before, the West considers the conclusion of SEKAY NO KANSEN 
Commentator Oh Rekhey [transliterated] to be timely... "Aren't 
the colossal expenditures on the construction of surface 
combatants senseless from the point of view of self-defense if 
we can sink these ships without hindrance..." That is why 
foreign navies are paying such serious attention to torpedo 
defense as a very important element of the self-defense of 
surface combatants and ships. 
  Today, it seems very important to painstakingly study 
leading 
foreign experience in the area of their effective defense from 
torpedoes when a new native concept of design and construction 
of surface combatants and ships is being developed. 
  COPYRIGHT: "Morskoy sbornik", 1994. 

