Note: M--magnetic firing mechanisms; A--acoustic; HD--hydrodynamic; 
S--seismic 


  Mines with a seismic firing mechanism present the greatest 
danger because, on one hand, they are buried in the ground as a 
rule, which makes finding and destroying them much harder and 
less effective, and on the other hand, they also have other 
back-up forms of firing mechanisms. Intensive development of 
such mines is making it necessary to study the fine structure of 
a ship's seismic field more carefully, and to seek ways and 
means of fighting these mines. 
  COPYRIGHT: "Morskoy sbornik", 1994. 

