<H3> <TI>   `Okean-SP' Coastal Radar Tracks Shipping Movements Off </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Okean-SP' Coastal Radar Tracks Shipping Movements Off </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Baltiysk 

<F P=102>   PM0606101594 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 2 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PM0606101594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Valeriy Gromak report: "Okean Changes Profession"] </F>
  [Text] Baltiysk -- The problem of ensuring the safety of 
warship and civilian vessel movement has always existed for 
Baltiysk. Today, considerably more Kaliningrad-bound foreign 
ships have started passing through the main base of the Baltic 
Fleet, which has made the problem of ensuring safety even more 
complex. The Russian Maritime Transportation Department has 
recently certified the fact of the creation in Baltiysk of the 
oblast's first coastal system of shipping movements. Its base 
is the "Okean-SP" coastal radar complex which can automatically 
track 55 targets at once. 

</TEXT>

