  [Text] On 23 May dock trials began at Severodvinsk on 
the new nuclear missile submarine `Kursk' commanded by Capt 1st 
Rank V. Rozhkov. 
  As pointed out by Ivan Vasilyev, in charge of releasing the 
order, the nuclear submarine has a number of improvements, 
including the navigational system, and improved living 
conditions for the crew. The new nuclear submarine will become a 
part of Russia's Navy in December of this year. 

